I am playing a troll shaman (Boogfit), while I am always going to have that nasty trollness going on in my head, I see him as more of a predator than evil.  He would hesitate for a second grouping with a high elf paladin if he thought it would help him.  <br>
<br>
Over time perhaps the paladin will prove his worth to Boogfit, and consider him an ally.  Then again, perhaps Boogfit will consider him a useful tool and kill him just as the Hackmaster+5 drops so Boogfit can loot it.<br>
<br>
As a reverse, perhaps the paladin sees Boogfit as merely a product of his the enviroment he was raised in and a potential power weapon for good if his trollish instincts can be controlled.<br>
<br>
In either case the alignment ruleset would hamper/prevent this.<br>
<br>
Perhaps a more well thought out system would work, however I think a MUCh greater flexibility in choosing alignments and gods would be necessary.  Maybe all troll shamans start out worshipping Innoruuk or Cazic Thule, but could do a quest to convert some of the other gods who would make sense and in doing so, change alignment.  Boogfit, for example, would probably DN as he just sees life as a natural environment where the strongest survive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.246g<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

